Document Description: Logbook, double facing page, 4 days per view
Vessel Movements: Maryport, Chanaral (Chile) via Cape Horn, Pisagua, and return to London via Cape Horn.
Atmospheric Pressure Instrument Exposure: Fixed in the chartroom, where there is no fire, height 22 feet outward, 20 feet homeward
Dry Bulb Thermometer exposure: Screen at break of poop deck, in the open air but screened from sun, rain and spray.
Wet Bulb Thermometer exposure: Screen at break of poop deck, in the open air but screened from sun, rain and spray.
Specific Gravity/Density: Hydrometer 1005 until 30/11, 1004 to end.  Daily observations.
Scale used for measuring Waves*: Directon of swell, Sea disturbance scale 0-9
Notes (Other Observations): 29/7 - SST of 30F recorded east of Drake Passage, no signs of ice from aloft.  31/7 - SST 29.8F,  Drift ice sighted.  3/8, 50S/50W, SST jumps from 36F to 51F between 8pm and midnight confirmed by testing.  Break in NE Trade, 2/10.
Comments: Poor agreement between barometer and aneroid prior to breakage of MO instrument.  Barometer may have been out of order for some time.
